  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You gather earth and rock around your fist, and you strike at your enemies in melee or in range. Make a spell attack roll against your target’s AC. On a success, you deal 1d8 bludgeoning damage. On a critical success, you deal double damage.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The range for this spell varies depending on the number of actions used to cast this spell; touch for 1 action, 30 feet for 2 actions.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u>Special:</u> While you are in Earthen Rage, you add your spellcasting ability modifier to the damage. As part of the spell, you can choose to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.7blmbDrQFNfdT731]{Shove} your target, using your Athletics or Nature for the roll against the target’s DC. If your spell attack is a critical hit, treat your roll as having one degree of success higher. Critical Failures on the attempt become Failures, instead.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Heightened(3rd)</strong> The damage for a success increases to 2d8 bludgeoning damage plus your spellcasting modifier.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Heightened(6th)</strong> The damage for a success increases to 3d8 bludgeoning damage plus your spellcasting modifier.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Heightened(9th)</strong> The damage for a success increases to 4d8 bludgeoning damage plus your spellcasting modifier.</p>"
    },
